titleStmt.title: The last words of William Parry a lawyer who suffered for endeavouring to depose the Queen's Highness, and bring in Q. Mary and her young son James.
titleStmt.author: Parry, William, d. 1585.

notesStmt.note: The apostrophe in "Queen's" is lightly printed.
